<div class="workbook-step">
  <h2>PROACTIVELY ENGAGE</h2>
  <p>Plan ahead: write down how you will <strong>GIVE</strong> the review.</p>

  <div class="context-box">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>G</strong>entle</li>
      <li><strong>I</strong>nterested</li>
      <li><strong>V</strong>alidate</li>
      <li><strong>E</strong>asy manner</li>
    </ul>
    <p><em>Example: "I can see a lot of effort and dedication went into this and I appreciate the approach you took. The code looks really solid, and it lays a good foundation for the new feature. I think you could move a couple constants created here to the settings file, but otherwise this code is very DRY. Great work!"</em></p>
  </div>

  <%= form_with model: workbook_session, url: workbook_session_path(workbook_session), method: :patch, id: "step-form" do |f| %>
    <%= f.hidden_field :current_step, value: "give_plan" %>
    <div class="field">
      <%= f.label :give_plan, "Your GIVE review:" %>
      <%= f.text_area :give_plan, rows: 5,
          placeholder: "Write your practice review here..." %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
